ce:section.ce:para:
PSCs were studied under light illumination for photoluminescence spectroscopy and UV–Vis absorption spectroscopy with Oscilla optical setup. JEOL, JSM-IT300 scanning microscopes were used to study the grain size and crystal structures of the materials. For PCE tests, the PSCs were subjected to a solar simulator of 1 sunlight intensity (1.5AM at 100 mW/cm2) of J-V curve measurement determining PCE, FF, open-circuit voltage (V

                        OC

                     ) and short-circuit current (J

                        SC
                     ) in Oscilla J-V setup utilizing Automated-S211 (T2003B) built-in software.
